  "skip_reason": "centered_2nd_uniform_latlon is a 2D structured stencil whose lon-axis coefficients carry the 1/(R cos_lat) sphere-geometry metric. The current ESS MMS harness (apply_stencil_periodic_1d in mms_evaluator.jl) only supports 1D periodic Cartesian stencils with scalar bindings dx/h, so it cannot exercise (a) the 2D selector dispatch (axis: lon | lat picking the right stencil pair), (b) the per-cell cos_lat binding that varies with latitude, or (c) a globally-smooth manufactured solution on the sphere (e.g. the Y_2,0 spherical harmonic the bead targets). Tracked for unblocking by follow-up bead dsc-7jc (ESS MMS harness: 2D structured + per-cell metric bindings + sphere MMS registry). Until that lands, the rule's mathematical claim (2nd order on a sphere away from poles) cannot be checked by the walker; the structural claims (rule discoverable, stencil shape, selector kind, AST coefficients including cos_lat) ARE checked by test/test_rule_catalog.jl."
